
[1]plodding

   PLOD'DING, ppr. Traveling or laboring with slow movement and steady
   diligence; studying closely but heavily.

   1. a. Industrious; diligent, but slow in contrivance or execution.

     PLOD'DING, n. Slow movement or study with steadiness or persevering
                                  industry.
